<paragraph id="8BBF36AEFFEAEF3F6253FB67FD02FB5D" blockId="5.[377,744,1186,1208]" box="[377,744,1186,1208]" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">
<heading id="D0F781C2FFEAEF3F6253FB67FD02FB5D" box="[377,744,1186,1208]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F6253FB67FD02FB5D" bold="true" box="[377,744,1186,1208]" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFEAEF3F6253FB67FDB1FB5D" authorityName="Britton" authorityYear="1948" box="[377,603,1186,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitreus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F6253FB67FDB1FB5D" bold="true" box="[377,603,1186,1208]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">Mecyclothorax vitreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31A6525FFEAEF3C6380FB0BFCE2FE92" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="389" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBF36AEFFEAEF3C6380FB0BFCE2FE92" blockId="5.[146,976,1230,1570]" lastBlockId="6.[175,1004,194,375]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="389" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F6380FB0BFEF8FB01" bold="true" box="[170,274,1230,1252]" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This group can be distinguished by: 1) glabrous pronotum with very narrow, posteriorly sinuate lateral margins; 2) presence of only the posterior supraorbital seta, the anterior seta being absent; 3) well-developed but not hemispherically convex eyes; 4) the presence of striae 1–2 to 1–5 on the elytral disc, but only the sutural stria 1 well-developed at elytral apex; and 5) reduced microsculpture, the dorsal surface glossy. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B5FFFEAEF3F616EFA97FD3CFA8D" author="Britton" box="[580,726,1362,1384]" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" pagination="107 - 166" refId="ref13531" refString="Britton, E. B. 1948. A revision of the Hawaiian species of Mecyclothorax (Coleoptera: Carabidae). Occasional Papers of the Bernice P. Bishop Museum 19: 107 - 166." type="journal article" year="1948">Britton (1948)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosed the group so that his three included species lacked elytral microsculpture, however, some individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFEAEF3F6207FA4DFDC3FA78" authority="(Sharp)" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[301,553,1415,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perkinsianus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F6207FA4DFE3BFA78" box="[301,465,1416,1437]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">M. perkinsianus</emphasis>
(Sharp)
</taxonomicName>
exhibit transverse mesh microsculpture over portions of the elytra. 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFEAEF3F6295FA67FD46FA52" authorityName="Liebherr" authorityYear="2009" box="[447,684,1442,1463]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F6295FA67FD46FA52" box="[447,684,1442,1463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">Mecyclothorax flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24757C7FFEAEF3F6197FA67FCDCFA5D" box="[701,822,1442,1464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
deviates from Britton’s diagnosis by having shallow transverse-mesh microsculpture over the entire elytra, though the surface appears glossy up to 80 
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F6033FA1DFCC7FA09" bold="true" box="[793,813,1496,1516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">3</emphasis>
magnification. However, among all Hawaiian 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFEAEF3F62F0FA37FD98F9E2" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1903" box="[474,626,1522,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F62F0FA37FD98F9E2" box="[474,626,1522,1543]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">Mecyclothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFEAEF3F61ABFA37FD19F9E2" authorityName="Liebherr" authorityYear="2009" box="[641,755,1522,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F61ABFA37FD19F9E2" box="[641,755,1522,1543]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">M. flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
agrees only with the species placed by Britton in his 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFEAEF3F62CEF9C8FDA7F9C7" authorityName="Britton" authorityYear="1948" box="[484,589,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitreus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFEAEF3F62CEF9C8FDA7F9C7" box="[484,589,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="388">M. vitreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group in the combination of glabrous pronotum and absence of the anterior supraorbital seta. As these are assuredly synapomorphies relative to the Hawaiian 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFE9EF3C61EDFF18FCB5FF17" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1903" box="[711,863,221,242]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C61EDFF18FCB5FF17" box="[711,863,221,242]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Mecyclothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ground-plan, the species group diagnosis is broadened to include 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFE9EF3C6193FF32FCC2FEE9" authorityName="Liebherr" authorityYear="2009" box="[697,808,247,268]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C6193FF32FCC2FEE9" box="[697,808,247,268]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">M. flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition to this single Lanai species, the species group also includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFE9EF3C61FFFED7FC24FECD" authority="(Blackburn)" baseAuthorityName="Blackburn" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[725,974,274,296]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deverilli">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C61FFFED7FCA0FEC2" box="[725,842,274,295]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">M. deverilli</emphasis>
(Blackburn)
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingRegion id="49C4F84CFFE9EF3C6385FEE9FF13FEA7" box="[175,249,300,322]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
Island, and two described species from East Maui, 
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C6037FEE8FCD0FEA7" box="[797,826,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFE9EF3C6060FEE8FF16FEB8" authority="(Sharp)" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perkinsianus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C6060FEE8FC06FEA7" box="[842,1004,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">M. perkinsianus</emphasis>
(Sharp)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D2DFFE9EF3C621AFE82FE0DFEB8" authority="Britton" authorityName="Britton" authorityYear="1948" box="[304,487,327,349]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitreus">
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C621AFE82FE7CFEB9" box="[304,406,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">M. vitreus</emphasis>
Britton
</taxonomicName>
from Haleakala Volcano (
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B5FFFE9EF3C61D2FE82FC97FEB8" author="Britton" box="[760,893,327,349]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" pagination="107 - 166" refId="ref13531" refString="Britton, E. B. 1948. A revision of the Hawaiian species of Mecyclothorax (Coleoptera: Carabidae). Occasional Papers of the Bernice P. Bishop Museum 19: 107 - 166." type="journal article" year="1948">Britton 1948</bibRefCitation>
). Contrary to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B5FFFE9EF3C63E6FEA4FE93FE92" author="Liebherr" box="[204,377,353,375]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" pagination="19 - 78" refId="ref14992" refString="Liebherr, J. K. 2008 b. Taxonomic revision of Mecyclothorax Sharp (Coleoptera, Carabidae) of Hawaii Island: abundant genitalic variation in a nascent island radiation. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitshrift 55: 19 - 78." type="journal article" year="2008">
Liebherr (2008 
<emphasis id="B974EABCFFE9EF3C624EFEA7FE9AFE92" box="[356,368,354,375]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">b</emphasis>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the group is not present on Molokai.
</paragraph>
